-- Toyota says to mull overseas bonus cuts, work-sharing
-- 
-- Fri Feb 6, 2009 2:04am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/02/06/us-toyota-bonus-sb-idUSTRE5151HB20090206

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) said on Friday it will discuss bonus cuts and work-sharing in its overseas operations, as the world's leading automaker struggles to cope with sliding sales. 

 Executive Vice President Mitsuo Kinoshita made the comment at a news conference following the release of Toyota's quarterly earnings results. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )